 width="400" height="791">
                  <br>
                  </td>
                </tr>
                                               
          </tbody>                                    
        </table>
                                                 
        <pre><big><big><big><font face="Verdana" size="3"
 color="#808080"><big>Who was speaking?</big></font></big></big></big><br><br>              </pre>
                 <big><big><br>
          </big></big>                                                   
       
        <div align="left"><big><big><font face="Verdana" size="2">     The
 spoken text at the start of the cylinder recording has been wrongly  attributed
 as belonging </font></big></big><big><big><font face="Verdana" size="2">to
 Brahms.  Numerous writers, scholars and amateurs  alike, have presumed that
 Brahms </font></big></big><big><big><font face="Verdana" size="2">introduces
 himself with the words "I am Doctor Brahms,  Johannes Brahms".</font></big></big><big><big><font
 face="Verdana" size="2"> However a humber of factors raise serious doubts
 as to who is speaking. The only mention of </font></big></big><big><big><font
 face="Verdana" size="2">the recording by someone who was present (in the
  published memoires of Fellinger's son) </font></big></big><big><big><font
 face="Verdana" size="2">states that Brahms was introduced. Considering the
  time between the announcement and </font></big></big><big><big><font
 face="Verdana" size="2">the start of the music it seems improbable that
the same person could segue from speech </font></big></big><big><big><font
 face="Verdana" size="2">to playing so quickly  particularly given the technological 
  limitations. </font></big></big><br>
             <big><big><font face="Verdana" size="2">     The denoised excerpts 
  reveals enough of the speech to suggest that the speaker (probably </font></big></big><big><big><font
 face="Verdana" size="2">Wangemann) introduces Brahms as follows:</font></big></big><br>
             <big><big><font face="Verdana" size="2"><br>
     "...Dezember Achtzehnhundertachtundneunzig. Haus von Herrn Doktor Fellinger, 
  bei mir ist</font></big></big><big><big><font face="Verdana" size="2"> Doktor
  Brahms, Johannes Brahms".</font></big></big><br>
             <big><big><font face="Verdana" size="2"><br>
     ("...December Eighteen Hundred Eighty Nine. House of Mr. Fellinger,
with   me is </font></big></big><big><big><font face="Verdana" size="2">Doctor 
Brahms,  Johannes Brahms."</font></big></big>)<br>
             <big><big><font face="Verdana" size="2"><br>
     (acknowledgements to Guido Behnke for his assistance in transcribing 
the   text)</font></big></big><br>
 </div>
        </div>
        </td>
                           <td valign="top" height="15%" width="15%">   
             <img rc="brahms2.gif" alt="" width="400" height="466"
 src="brahms2.gif">
          <br>
          <br>
